    "en": {
      "title": "Another batch of aid from India",
      "author": "unknown",
      "body_lines": [
        "The Indian High Commissioner to Sri Lanka today (26) presented to Sri Lanka a consignment of goods worth over 40 million dollars worth of rice, milk and medicines donated by Tamil Nadu.",
        "40,000 metric tons of rice, 500 metric tons of milk powder and more than 100 metric tons of medicines worth 22 million dollars are included in this stock of goods and the Minister of Foreign Affairs Ali Sabri and the Minister of Health Mr. Keheliya Rambukwella accepted the stock of goods."
      ],
